    <description>Takes in a phone number and looks for a related record across Contact, Account and Lead. To be used with linking Messaging Users/Sessions and Voice Calls</description>
    <formulas>
        <description>If the + is in the search string then we need to remove it or the Apex fails, but it will still mach on a phone number field starting with a plus +</description>
        <name>SearchString</name>
        <dataType>String</dataType>
        <expression>IF(LEFT({!NumberToSearchWith},1) == &quot;+&quot; , &quot;(&quot; +  RIGHT({!NumberToSearchWith}, LEN({!NumberToSearchWith})-1) + &quot;) OR (&quot; + {!StrippedNumber} + &quot;)&quot;, {!StrippedNumber})</expression>
    </formulas>
    <formulas>
        <description>For Voice and Messaging the number will have a + followed by the country code. We just want the main number without this, so we strip it out.
We also need to strip out hyphens which turn up when using Lightning Dialer</description>
        <name>StrippedNumber</name>
        <dataType>String</dataType>
        <expression>IF(LEFT({!NumberToSearchWith}, 1) == &quot;+&quot;, IF(LEFT({!NumberToSearchWith}, 2) == &quot;+1&quot;, 
        RIGHT({!NumberToSearchWith}, LEN({!NumberToSearchWith})-2), 
        RIGHT({!NumberToSearchWith}, LEN({!NumberToSearchWith})-3)
    ),
SUBSTITUTE({!NumberToSearchWith},&quot;-&quot;,&quot;&quot;))</expression>
    </formulas>
